datsit is a free digital platform that operates as an intermediary between selected cultural tourism operators and international consumers of Italian products/experiences.
Operating at the same time as a storytelling, experience certification and consumer incentive tool, the datsit system is built on people-based mapping of the territory, on the aggregation of selected operators and their offerings on the proprietary digital platform and on the facilitation of interaction between them and consumers, proposing a model driven by the enthusiasm of the entire community and on the responsibility of those who do business. 
datsit offers consumers:
-A diversified and selected database of Italian products/experiences around the world;
-Selected contents presented with a friendly and engaging interface that goes beyond a simple description but respects, enhances and narrates the uniqueness of the individual operators;
-A cashback on every purchase directly spendable through the platform;
-Direct and facilitated interaction with operators for bookings and purchase information;
-The guarantee of the authenticity and quality of the products offered;
-The possibility of receiving personalised content and tourist itineraries based on one's consumption habits;
-The suggestion of new cross-sector consumption experiences;
-The possibility of interacting directly with other consumers to share tips and experiences.
datsit is based on a consumer incentive process designed to build consumer loyalty to the brand Italia. In concrete terms, datsit withholds a fee for every purchase made within the system, returning part of it directly to the user and binding its use to consumption within the platform. datsit makes it possible to trace the entire path of consumption of each user with the brand Italia, from the first interaction in the user's country of origin, to the tourist experience on Italian territory, offering opportunities for customer profiling that do not exist to date.

Tedtrip – Italian Style Experiences is a project of Sustainable Experiential Tourism, with SocialTech characterization, i.e. as a search for new products and services able to offer technological solutions that respond to contemporary challenges in terms of economic, social, and environmental sustainability. Tedtrip therefore aligns perfectly with UN Sustainable Development Goal (SDGs); in particular to: 
- SDG 3 GOOD HEALTH: ENSURING A HEALTHY LIFE AND PROMOTING THE WELL-BEING OF ALL AT ALL AGES;
Tedtrip promotes the activation of emotional circulation, which is the basis of psychophysical well-being and the success of every human being. In the post covid this UN goal is particularly requested by the traveler, and therefore Tedtrip will take care of the health safety of all experiential tourist activities offered. 
- SDG 4 EDUCATION: PROMOTING QUALITY, INCLUSIVE AND EQUAL EDUCATION AND ENSURING LIFELONG LEARNING OPPORTUNITIES FOR ALL;
Tedtrip research and in-depth work in the field of Tourism Sciences, and in particular experiential tourism and new digital media, has led to the development of a method for the creation of experiential tourism skills (our TEDs), which is the content of our training program
- SDG 17 STRENGTHENING IMPLEMENTATION ARRANGEMENTS RELAUNCHING THE GLOBAL PARTNERSHIP FOR SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT;
Tedtrip is a platform based on a CMS local portal , tedtrip.eu for the presentation of Experiences, linked to Trekksoft, a multichannel-management tool for sale in the main OTAs and in traditonal Trekksoft partner TOs . The Tedtrip project it introduces TED professionals (Travel Emotion Designer) , the designers of travel emotions, who with a deep knowledge of place and activities they propose, have the task of interpreting and enhancing the material and immaterial heritage territories. 

The TEDs participating in the training course developed by Tedtrip team, learn the method for creating high quality Experiences to be resold by TEDTRIP paltform. This way TEDTRIP ensures a quality tourism offer which other OTAs can't ensure.

Ombrellone was founded in 2021 as an innovative start-up, with the aim of proposing to the market a platform for booking/rental umbrellas at beach establishments, aiming to develop local and international market. The business model is based on booking/rental beach umbrellas to those who have a seasonal umbrella to put back on sale when they are not being used (C2C), a super plus business idea. In addition to OTA model, we add a management system for beach establishments and web app oriented to add on services.  All developed directly by Ombrellone.it, adding the SaaS model to the company's business model. This year, thanks to a few strategic partnerships with important players, the R2R model will also be tested.
The solutions and opportunities to be grasped are, starting from the assumption that focus should be on the traveller/vacationist daily experience, who wants:
- be able to book  or rental a beach umbrella in advance, without having to risk wasting time, or not finding an available establishment that meets all their needs in terms of personal requirements, values and commodities offered; 
- being able to select the establishment according to his or her most personal needs such as: location, costs, additional services, audience (singles, families, etc.), food, pet friendly, sea caring, etc.
 The seasonal traveller/vacationist wants to:
- freely decide whether to go to the beach in that specific place, or alternatively be able to earn money by booking or renting their own beach umbrella place.	
The beach establishment needs to increase its turnover and maximise the average daily revenue from a beach umbrella place:
- Needs a tool to know occupancy and revenue data (management);
- Needs a tool to propose in real time to its customers the add on services to be provided, activating upselling strategies (webapp);
- Needs a tool to preside over the web trying to acquire tourists (organic leads) and not seasonal customers. The tourist comes to spend more than 20 times the seasonal for each day of stay (OTA model platform);
- There is a vital need for a tool to put 'dormant' seasonal umbrellas back on the market when not occupied or used (OTA and C2C model platform)
To conclude, with ombrellone.it we want to propose: 
- an online platform, native app and web portal that allows anyone using a digital device to be able to book or rent in advance, from the comfort of their home or while moving on last minute/not only holidays, the best umbrella beach place
